WEBVTT

00:00.042 --> 00:02.060
<i>Previously on "Once Upon A Time"...</i>

00:02.085 --> 00:03.979
- Kill him.
- Why? I don't understand.

00:04.003 --> 00:05.564
I don't need you to understand.

00:05.589 --> 00:06.982
I need you to obey.

00:07.007 --> 00:08.074
HENRY: Look. Whatever
she wants you to do to me,

00:08.098 --> 00:09.207
you don't have to do it.

00:09.309 --> 00:12.210
You seem a lot nicer. I'm not.

00:12.235 --> 00:13.565
I've seen your cold case.

00:13.590 --> 00:14.724
The one with the missing girl.

00:14.748 --> 00:16.262
MAN: That's one powerful rune.

00:16.286 --> 00:17.782
If your lost girl was drawin' that,

00:17.884 --> 00:20.252
I'd hate to meet whatever
evil she was facing down.

00:20.354 --> 00:21.486
You wanted to see me?

00:21.588 --> 00:22.721
RONI: I found this.

00:22.746 --> 00:24.556
I have no idea who that kid is.

00:24.658 --> 00:26.324
I do.

00:26.503 --> 00:27.503
That's me.

00:29.000 --> 00:35.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:38.231 --> 00:40.431
This is supposed to
be a scene from my book

00:40.456 --> 00:42.650
with us photoshopped
in as the characters.

00:42.675 --> 00:45.441
This me as the kid who
believes in Fairy Tales,

00:45.466 --> 00:47.667
and you as my mom.

00:48.515 --> 00:49.881
The Evil Queen.

00:50.376 --> 00:53.418
The Evil Queen?

00:54.621 --> 00:57.756
Right. So Victoria's screwing with us.

00:57.858 --> 00:58.869
Whoa! Whoa, whoa, whoa!

00:58.894 --> 01:00.892
Hey, hey, slow down there, Babe Ruth.

01:01.071 --> 01:02.104
Geez.

01:02.129 --> 01:04.062
We don't know that
Victoria made the photo.

01:04.164 --> 01:08.533
Can we at least look into it
before it's clobberin' time?

01:11.705 --> 01:12.804
Roni.

01:12.906 --> 01:15.740
I am so glad you're still here.

01:16.977 --> 01:18.510
Hey, uh, what's up?

01:18.612 --> 01:20.612
It's, um... it's been a big night.

01:20.714 --> 01:25.744
Sabine and I, uh, we sort
of bought a food truck.

01:26.104 --> 01:27.471
Well, that's great.

01:27.496 --> 01:29.198
It needs a lot of work,
and I sold my tools.

01:29.222 --> 01:30.268
Do you have any?

01:30.293 --> 01:32.624
Well, lucky for you, this
place is falling apart, so...

01:34.661 --> 01:37.429
I've got all the tools you'll need.

01:37.531 --> 01:39.497
You are a lifesaver.

01:39.902 --> 01:41.129
Well, hey.

01:41.154 --> 01:44.969
Um, If you need some help,
I'm pretty good around engines,

01:45.072 --> 01:46.471
you know, for a writer.

01:46.573 --> 01:48.673
No, I'm fine.

01:51.596 --> 01:53.462
[DOOR CLOSES]

01:54.345 --> 01:55.642
What was that?

01:55.699 --> 01:57.366
Hey, if I were the Evil Queen,

01:57.468 --> 02:00.406
I could look into my
magic mirror and tell you.

02:01.305 --> 02:04.206
But this is all the magic I got.

02:06.343 --> 02:08.110
[BOTTLES CLINK]

02:11.014 --> 02:15.150
HENRY: Okay, Zen and the art
of fixing a busted motorcycle.

02:15.252 --> 02:18.887
First lesson... Know thy tools.

02:18.989 --> 02:21.790
Starting with the humble torque wrench.

02:22.326 --> 02:25.127
I like this... torque wrench.

02:26.497 --> 02:28.730
Thanks for letting me help. Really.

02:31.307 --> 02:33.546
The magical carriage is real.

02:33.571 --> 02:35.837
Bet it's worth its weight in gold.

02:37.785 --> 02:39.129
And let me guess... You fine fellows

02:39.153 --> 02:42.054
are here to kill us and take it?

02:42.079 --> 02:44.381
Hey, he's smarter than he looks.

02:44.406 --> 02:45.948
Yeah.

02:46.448 --> 02:48.314
Good thing you're not.

03:02.019 --> 03:03.618
Get away from my son.

03:04.770 --> 03:06.739
It's okay, Mom. I got this.

03:16.524 --> 03:18.023
[BODY THUDS]

03:18.048 --> 03:20.649
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

03:26.464 --> 03:28.031
Well, I guess you do
know how to use a wrench.

03:28.055 --> 03:29.488
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

03:32.846 --> 03:34.882
Henry, you okay?

03:34.907 --> 03:37.975
Oh, yeah. I'm fine.
Nothing we can't handle.

03:40.337 --> 03:42.404
Thanks to this.

03:42.473 --> 03:44.504
You still have it.

03:45.450 --> 03:46.502
[CHUCKLES]

03:46.527 --> 03:49.862
You know, I bought this
for you when you were 10.

03:51.655 --> 03:53.555
And now here you are

03:53.856 --> 03:58.353
with a sword and motorcycle and a girl.

03:58.677 --> 04:02.591
Yeah, still figuring the girl part out.

04:02.693 --> 04:04.359
The Resistance always come first, right?

04:04.740 --> 04:07.040
As soon as we fix up the bike,

04:07.065 --> 04:08.969
we're off on another recon mission.

04:08.994 --> 04:11.649
Oh, that sounds dangerous.

04:11.674 --> 04:13.845
Hey, you should come with us.

04:13.870 --> 04:14.870
We could use you.

04:15.846 --> 04:17.372
I can't.

04:17.517 --> 04:19.817
- I-I'm busy.
- With what?

04:19.843 --> 04:21.843
Don't tell me you're going
on naval patrol with Hook.

04:21.867 --> 04:24.546
[CHUCKLING] Not if I can help it.

04:24.615 --> 04:26.848
But you don't need your
mother around you all the time.

04:26.950 --> 04:29.384
Not anymore.

04:29.953 --> 04:32.564
And obviously, you can
take care of yourself.

04:32.666 --> 04:33.565
So...

04:33.590 --> 04:35.457
[SIGHS]

04:38.495 --> 04:40.395
Be safe.

04:42.399 --> 04:44.066
[HORN HONKS]

04:44.134 --> 04:45.921
- [DOOR OPENS]
- IVY: Are you feeling all right, Mother?

04:45.945 --> 04:46.756
Yes, Ivy.

04:46.781 --> 04:49.404
I'm lying here in the dark
because I feel fantastic.

04:50.100 --> 04:51.263
It's a migraine.

04:51.288 --> 04:53.474
Did you put the wrong
sugar in my coffee?

04:53.499 --> 04:55.106
I told you aspartame is a trigger.

04:55.131 --> 04:57.045
I know, Mother, which
is why I always put

04:57.147 --> 04:59.330
real sugar in your coffee.

04:59.799 --> 05:01.983
You know, something else
might have triggered it.

05:02.086 --> 05:03.712
Like these flowers.

05:03.737 --> 05:05.387
I'm sure they're full of pollen.

05:05.489 --> 05:08.134
Why don't you let me get rid
of the revolting things for you?

05:08.159 --> 05:09.201
[SIGHS] Fine.

05:09.226 --> 05:11.547
Anything to make your
grating voice stop.

05:20.270 --> 05:22.070
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

05:29.751 --> 05:31.050
You got them!

05:32.149 --> 05:34.483
Give them here. I can't wait any longer.

05:35.053 --> 05:36.318
Ah!

05:37.036 --> 05:39.331
So, do they have the magic we need?

05:39.934 --> 05:41.840
Only the tiniest seed.

05:42.426 --> 05:44.336
But it's still quite fragile.

05:44.361 --> 05:45.761
It needs fertile ground.

05:45.863 --> 05:47.929
I suppose I'm to get that, too?

05:48.031 --> 05:51.801
I have spent too much time
in this world fetching things.

05:52.369 --> 05:55.237
You must be patient a
little longer, my dear.

05:55.305 --> 05:57.939
Remember what I taught you.

05:58.041 --> 06:00.809
Remember how we survive.

06:00.911 --> 06:03.211
I know.

06:03.313 --> 06:05.814
I close my eyes.

06:05.916 --> 06:09.484
I imagine my mother's destruction.

06:09.586 --> 06:12.687
Mother isn't the only one to be wary of.

06:16.059 --> 06:17.492
Regina.

06:17.928 --> 06:20.996
I'm not sure it was wise
to give her the photo.

06:21.695 --> 06:23.965
Oh, don't worry.

06:24.001 --> 06:29.271
By the end of the day,
Regina won't be a problem.

06:30.750 --> 06:31.896
[DOOR CLOSES]

06:31.921 --> 06:33.241
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYS ON STEREO]

06:33.687 --> 06:35.975
Okay, so I figured out the mystery.

06:36.000 --> 06:38.346
Look, Ivy's timeline from Halloween.

06:38.415 --> 06:41.235
She posted a bunch of pictures
of us getting drinks together.

06:41.415 --> 06:42.921
Oh, this looks bad.

06:42.946 --> 06:45.140
"#Drunkoween"?

06:45.165 --> 06:46.799
# DrinkingBuddy.

06:46.824 --> 06:47.824
Yeah, this looks bad.

06:47.858 --> 06:49.658
Well, that's why I'm
not on social media.

06:49.760 --> 06:50.859
Yeah, but Jacinda is.

06:50.928 --> 06:51.712
And now I'm worried

06:51.737 --> 06:54.204
- that whatever we had, I screwed it all up.
- [DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

06:54.228 --> 06:56.198
I want to see the picture!

06:56.266 --> 06:57.933
How do you know about the picture, Lucy?

06:58.035 --> 06:59.843
Ivy told me all about it.

06:59.868 --> 07:01.636
She did? She...

07:02.706 --> 07:04.373
Oh, boy.

07:07.367 --> 07:09.333
This photo.

07:09.358 --> 07:10.645
I know she's on your side now,

07:10.714 --> 07:12.903
and I know what you found
in Grandma's weird attic,

07:12.928 --> 07:14.089
so come on!

07:14.119 --> 07:15.652
Show me!

07:17.732 --> 07:19.131
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

07:19.156 --> 07:20.589
Wait a minute.

07:20.657 --> 07:22.982
I remember reading this scene.

07:23.045 --> 07:26.728
Um, so, Henry is Henry, obviously,

07:27.049 --> 07:30.739
and Roni, you're...

07:33.048 --> 07:34.518
[GASPS LIGHTLY]

07:34.543 --> 07:37.277
You're Regina! I mean,
of course you are!

07:37.302 --> 07:39.049
Oh, my gosh. You're his mom.

07:39.074 --> 07:43.290
Regina Mills adopted Henry Mills
in the real world in Boston!

07:43.315 --> 07:45.931
And it was the best thing that
ever happened to her, to you!

07:45.956 --> 07:47.851
Lucy, no.

07:47.876 --> 07:49.127
Give it up.

07:49.152 --> 07:50.919
The picture's obviously fake.

07:51.021 --> 07:52.387
No, it's not!

07:52.456 --> 07:54.723
Henry, you had something magical.

07:54.825 --> 07:57.692
You had a book that
had real stories in it,

07:58.118 --> 07:59.231
and you never gave up.

07:59.256 --> 08:00.973
And <i> I</i> won't give up, either.

08:01.075 --> 08:02.992
You are going to break this curse

08:03.017 --> 08:05.400
because you truly are Regina.

08:05.579 --> 08:07.913
And all I have to do
is make you remember.

08:07.938 --> 08:09.037
[SNAPS FINGERS]

08:09.106 --> 08:11.773
And I know exactly how to do it.

08:19.249 --> 08:21.332
WEAVER: This is where
the real suffering begins.

08:21.357 --> 08:23.103
Desk work isn't that bad.

08:23.128 --> 08:26.663
I feel fine. I'm going back to work.

08:26.732 --> 08:29.253
Well, Captain wants you to
stick it out for at least a week.

08:29.278 --> 08:31.501
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

08:37.645 --> 08:38.953
I take it you want to walk out of here.

08:38.977 --> 08:40.510
That's right. I'm going to walk

08:40.578 --> 08:43.874
straight back to the precinct,
have a word with the captain.

08:43.899 --> 08:46.416
In the meantime, keep
your eyes on your phone.

08:46.518 --> 08:48.318
I might have some
errands for you to run.

08:58.468 --> 09:01.336
I was hoping you might help
me while Weaver's resting up.

09:01.636 --> 09:03.833
It's an important case.
It's a missing girl.

09:03.902 --> 09:08.605
So, what do you and Weaver
do when he needs help?

09:08.707 --> 09:10.307
Mm...

09:13.107 --> 09:15.040
He buys me lunch.

09:16.986 --> 09:18.585
All right.

09:25.255 --> 09:28.254
Well, I was a little skeptical

09:28.279 --> 09:30.038
with the stray dogs
hanging out in the alley,

09:30.062 --> 09:31.766
but Bella Notte has damn good pizza.

09:31.791 --> 09:34.158
[CHUCKLES]

09:35.300 --> 09:37.518
Now, what's up with you?

09:38.403 --> 09:39.602
What do you mean?

09:39.671 --> 09:42.739
You've been quiet ever since
Lucy dropped the Regina bomb.

09:43.102 --> 09:45.275
Are you worried about her?

09:45.377 --> 09:46.276
No, it's not that.

09:46.378 --> 09:47.805
It just, you know...

09:48.953 --> 09:51.781
It just brought up a
difficult memory is all.

09:55.620 --> 09:59.322
[CHUCKLES] I actually... I...

09:59.424 --> 10:01.691
I did try to adopt once.

10:04.196 --> 10:06.763
A beautiful baby boy.

10:06.865 --> 10:09.833
Then at the last minute,
the adoption agency decided

10:09.935 --> 10:11.735
I wasn't a good fit.

10:16.208 --> 10:17.974
Just left a mark, you know?

10:18.043 --> 10:20.910
Well, for what it's worth,

10:21.013 --> 10:23.513
you seem like mom to a
lot of people around here.

10:25.617 --> 10:27.751
Which is why we have to help Lucy.

10:28.481 --> 10:30.697
If we pretend we believe her,

10:30.722 --> 10:32.389
then she'll stop being defensive

10:32.491 --> 10:35.392
and finally believe the
truth when she sees it.

10:35.705 --> 10:37.460
Trust me.

10:37.496 --> 10:41.744
The sooner the fantasy fades,
the sooner she can heal.

10:41.806 --> 10:44.100
Okay, Operation Heartbreak it is.

10:44.202 --> 10:45.101
Hmm?

10:45.170 --> 10:46.536
That's a thing from my book.

10:46.605 --> 10:48.271
Just like something else she said,

10:48.340 --> 10:50.473
which gives me a good idea
of exactly where she is.

10:50.542 --> 10:52.542
- You want to go there now?
- I'll go solo.

10:52.644 --> 10:56.124
Your afternoon is already full.

10:56.694 --> 10:57.924
Is it?

10:57.949 --> 10:59.049
Oh, did I forget to mention

10:59.117 --> 11:04.554
the pizza place was close to that?

11:05.824 --> 11:07.317
Go ask her out.

11:07.342 --> 11:11.327
Sometimes I guess you just got
to accept when Mom knows best.

11:11.396 --> 11:14.197
Now, be charming, and don't slouch.

11:16.802 --> 11:18.668
[CHUCKLES] I'm kidding!

11:18.770 --> 11:21.204
Go talk to her. I'll go deal with Lucy.

11:53.308 --> 11:56.109
[PLANT HISSES]

11:59.311 --> 12:00.743
[ROARS]

12:00.846 --> 12:02.879
Watch out!

12:08.920 --> 12:11.788
You have to be careful
around strange magic.

12:11.890 --> 12:14.057
You all right?

12:16.027 --> 12:17.594
Drizella.

12:18.806 --> 12:20.889
I should have let that thing eat you.

12:20.914 --> 12:22.647
You tried to kill my son.

12:22.672 --> 12:24.367
On my mother's orders.

12:24.469 --> 12:26.169
She doesn't take "no" for an answer.

12:26.617 --> 12:27.971
Well, is that why you're here?

12:28.039 --> 12:29.606
No.

12:29.674 --> 12:32.442
I am through with doing
things for that woman.

12:32.511 --> 12:36.613
I am here to find magic
to help me get free of her.

12:36.638 --> 12:37.803
Uh, what are you talking about?

12:37.827 --> 12:40.396
I thought you were marrying some prince.

12:41.286 --> 12:44.654
Do you honestly think
that was my choice?

12:46.803 --> 12:47.868
[METAL CLANKS]

12:48.339 --> 12:50.426
Oh, I see.

12:52.063 --> 12:55.899
The funny thing is,
I was born with magic.

12:56.010 --> 12:57.677
Only Mother never let me cultivate it.

12:57.702 --> 13:00.103
She knew I would only
use it to escape from her.

13:01.573 --> 13:03.673
So, if I can't learn
to use my own magic,

13:03.775 --> 13:06.309
I will steal someone else's.

13:06.334 --> 13:07.577
Drizella, I know what it's like

13:07.646 --> 13:10.580
to live with such a controlling mother.

13:12.884 --> 13:14.584
Perhaps I can help.

13:15.453 --> 13:16.934
Really?

13:18.300 --> 13:21.568
But you're not going to steal it.

13:21.593 --> 13:26.796
You're going to use the
gift you were born with.

13:27.326 --> 13:29.232
I got what you asked for.

13:29.312 --> 13:31.478
Fresh from that charmless
little community garden.

13:31.503 --> 13:33.503
Thank you.

13:33.572 --> 13:37.240
Your mother has denied me
of this for far too long.

13:37.607 --> 13:40.387
Then prove to me that this
was worth ruining my nails for.

14:15.189 --> 14:16.856
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

14:16.881 --> 14:20.583
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

14:22.887 --> 14:24.320
That's perfect.

14:24.499 --> 14:26.266
Careful!

14:26.423 --> 14:29.824
This is a most dangerous
path to take a person down.

14:37.769 --> 14:40.236
Then I guess we'll see

14:40.883 --> 14:44.455
if Regina is as powerful
as she thinks she is.

14:52.850 --> 14:53.949
[BUTTON CLICKS]

14:54.018 --> 14:57.052
[BRITISH NEW WAVE MUSIC PLAYS ON STEREO]

15:07.731 --> 15:08.830
What's that?

15:08.899 --> 15:10.219
♪ <i>Two dozen other dirty lovers</i> ♪

15:10.267 --> 15:12.901
Uh, The English Beat.
"Save it for Later."

15:13.003 --> 15:14.870
I know what it is.
Why are you playing it?

15:14.939 --> 15:16.283
♪ <i>Cry, cry, but I don't need my mother</i> ♪

15:16.307 --> 15:18.040
Oh, I always just liked the '80s.

15:18.142 --> 15:20.442
You know, John Hughes
movies, New Wave music...

15:20.511 --> 15:22.222
A little... little New
Order, a little Adam Ant.

15:22.246 --> 15:24.424
You know, I always used to make
these amazing mix tapes, and I was...

15:24.448 --> 15:27.515
You are making less sense
than normal, Henry Mills.

15:27.843 --> 15:29.685
Yeah, right. Uh... [CLEARS THROAT]

15:29.710 --> 15:32.006
♪ <i>Sooner or later</i> ♪

15:32.319 --> 15:35.123
Last time I was single,
mix tapes always worked

15:35.192 --> 15:38.327
when I wanted to ask a girl out, so...

15:38.395 --> 15:40.596
You're asking me on a date now?

15:40.698 --> 15:42.042
You sure it's me you want to ask out?

15:42.066 --> 15:42.967
Yes! Yes!

15:42.992 --> 15:44.415
Because the thing with
Ivy, that was a mistake.

15:44.439 --> 15:45.946
I mean, it wasn't,
like, a mistake mistake,

15:45.970 --> 15:48.241
- because nothing happened, but...
- Sorry.

15:48.266 --> 15:49.916
I get it. I get it. You
don't have to explain.

15:49.940 --> 15:50.973
But I do!

15:51.041 --> 15:52.285
I do because I find
myself wanting to explain

15:52.309 --> 15:53.389
all kinds of things to you,

15:53.444 --> 15:54.876
like... like, I don't know,

15:54.979 --> 15:57.294
like why pancakes are
appropriate for dessert,

15:57.319 --> 16:00.148
why the English Beat is
so culturally relevant,

16:00.217 --> 16:03.719
why I can't stop thinking about you.

16:05.615 --> 16:06.615
Wow.

16:08.092 --> 16:10.880
You sure have seen a lot
of John Hughes movies.

16:10.974 --> 16:13.528
[CHUCKLES]

16:13.597 --> 16:14.830
What if I explained to you

16:14.898 --> 16:17.633
that I have a daughter
and a new small business

16:17.735 --> 16:21.169
and very little time?

16:21.282 --> 16:22.915
Well, then I'd say, I'm a Swyft driver

16:22.940 --> 16:24.706
and a failed writer
with nothing but time.

16:25.383 --> 16:30.212
So, whenever you have some, I'd, uh...

16:30.281 --> 16:32.076
I'd love to take you on a date.

16:32.873 --> 16:34.783
Okay.

16:34.852 --> 16:36.618
What about now?

16:37.053 --> 16:39.588
Now? Like... Like, here? Like...

16:39.657 --> 16:41.523
Well, you said you're
good with cars, right?

16:41.625 --> 16:43.992
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

16:44.094 --> 16:47.896
And yeah, mix tapes always work.

16:47.965 --> 16:50.532
♪ <i>Run away, run away,</i>
<i>run away, run away</i> ♪

16:50.634 --> 16:53.802
[GRUNTS]

16:55.984 --> 16:57.283
[CHUCKLES]

16:57.308 --> 16:59.707
Yeah, thanks. Um...

17:00.511 --> 17:02.577
I'm just gonna...

17:02.804 --> 17:04.537
[VOLUME INCREASES]

17:06.016 --> 17:09.117
[GRUNTS] All right. Let's
see what we got going on.

17:09.219 --> 17:12.354
Okay. I'm going to test you now.

17:12.455 --> 17:14.790
Oh, yeah. There's the problem.

17:14.858 --> 17:16.525
- [CHUCKLES]
- I see it already.

17:16.593 --> 17:18.162
♪ <i>Run away</i> ♪

17:26.303 --> 17:28.303
[SIGHS]

17:32.718 --> 17:35.686
Thought Victoria said
you couldn't come here.

17:36.454 --> 17:37.646
[SIGHS]

17:39.083 --> 17:42.050
She doesn't know I'm here.

17:42.152 --> 17:43.485
And I had to come.

17:43.510 --> 17:44.986
Henry guessed you'd be here.

17:45.187 --> 17:46.887
Of course he did.

17:47.213 --> 17:50.459
Because when Henry
needed magic the most,

17:50.494 --> 17:55.297
the storybook showed up for
him in Snow White's closet.

17:57.668 --> 18:00.769
And when some people touch it,

18:00.871 --> 18:03.905
they remember everything
about who they were.

18:03.974 --> 18:10.479
Wow. So, if I grabbed it,

18:11.075 --> 18:12.881
I'd remember being a queen?

18:12.983 --> 18:14.950
You're never going to believe it.

18:15.778 --> 18:21.289
Look, I would love to
believe I was a queen.

18:21.358 --> 18:23.558
You know, someone with
this big, amazing life

18:23.660 --> 18:25.658
who adopted a son she loved.

18:25.683 --> 18:27.673
And I know enough to know

18:27.698 --> 18:29.731
I don't know everything, Lucy.

18:29.800 --> 18:34.102
So why don't we prove
this thing together?

18:34.898 --> 18:35.982
Really?

18:37.875 --> 18:39.469
What do you say?

18:40.234 --> 18:41.603
Partners?

18:43.773 --> 18:45.180
[CHUCKLES]

18:48.296 --> 18:50.240
You can do this, Drizella.

18:50.371 --> 18:51.888
[SIGHS]

18:53.056 --> 18:55.857
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

18:58.195 --> 19:00.061
I can't.

19:00.164 --> 19:01.530
I'm sorry I'm wasting your time.

19:01.598 --> 19:03.009
I'm sure you have better things to do.

19:03.033 --> 19:05.424
You're not wasting my time.

19:05.573 --> 19:07.068
[SIGHS]

19:07.831 --> 19:12.974
You just need... the right motivation.

19:13.076 --> 19:15.076
[STONE CRUMBLING]

19:22.891 --> 19:24.524
Regina! No!

19:29.489 --> 19:31.105
[CHUCKLES]

19:31.862 --> 19:33.094
[CHUCKLES]

19:33.163 --> 19:34.863
I-I didn't think I could do it.

19:34.932 --> 19:37.899
I didn't... I didn't
know it was possible.

19:38.001 --> 19:41.603
If you believe in yourself, it is.

19:43.774 --> 19:45.182
You know,

19:47.144 --> 19:49.578
you are a lot like I
was when I was your age.

19:52.249 --> 19:53.882
Except I didn't have the right guide,

19:53.951 --> 19:59.888
so all my power came
from anger and hate.

20:00.453 --> 20:01.500
I sought revenge,

20:01.525 --> 20:04.226
and I did terrible things to get it.

20:05.359 --> 20:07.629
I cast a dark curse.

20:08.351 --> 20:10.899
Did it give you what you wanted?

20:11.882 --> 20:13.435
For a while.

20:15.606 --> 20:18.073
Turns out I wanted the wrong things.

20:20.533 --> 20:26.147
The only thing that truly made
me happy was my son, Henry.

20:26.681 --> 20:29.317
I wish I had a mother like you.

20:31.121 --> 20:33.355
RUMPLESTILTSKIN: Don't we all?

20:35.392 --> 20:37.292
Rumple?

20:40.280 --> 20:41.630
It's a get-well gift.

20:42.733 --> 20:44.533
How can I help you, Roni?

20:46.603 --> 20:48.737
Can you find out

20:48.805 --> 20:54.409
if a certain woman applied
to adopt a baby in Boston?

20:54.511 --> 20:56.278
I'm not sure about the year.

20:56.486 --> 20:58.086
Her name's Regina Mills.

21:01.340 --> 21:04.719
That bought you this conversation.

21:04.821 --> 21:07.822
Now, what would make
me want to take this on?

21:13.096 --> 21:14.863
I'll owe you one.

21:18.302 --> 21:20.835
Then we have a deal.

21:26.869 --> 21:29.636
[TRAIN HORN BLOWS]

21:32.633 --> 21:35.534
How about a rematch while we chat?

21:35.566 --> 21:37.133
Games keep me focused.

21:37.305 --> 21:41.273
So, come on. I'll begin.

21:41.781 --> 21:43.909
Look, shouldn't we at
least reset the board?

21:43.934 --> 21:45.800
Why would we do that?

21:45.913 --> 21:48.113
Things are always more fun
when you start in the middle.

21:55.397 --> 21:59.600
So, tell me about Eloise Gardener.

22:00.528 --> 22:03.429
Um, until she disappeared 10 years ago,

22:03.497 --> 22:05.564
she was a normal kid.

22:05.666 --> 22:08.367
Liked art, hated school.

22:08.436 --> 22:10.636
She as a bit of an amateur poet.

22:10.705 --> 22:14.873
Well, that's everything,
except that she was fearless...

22:14.942 --> 22:18.277
until she disappeared when
something spooked her...

22:22.789 --> 22:24.189
something that was in this journal,

22:24.218 --> 22:28.187
something... some kind
of protection rune.

22:28.256 --> 22:30.723
Uh, it's... it's... it's complicated.

22:30.791 --> 22:32.591
Look, all that matters

22:32.627 --> 22:36.662
is why she disappeared
and where she is, so...

22:36.731 --> 22:38.931
[SIGHS]

22:38.956 --> 22:40.866
What am I missing? You know?

22:43.304 --> 22:45.862
Look at the board, Detective.

22:46.018 --> 22:48.626
You need to take a
good look at your side.

22:48.651 --> 22:50.119
What pieces do you already have

22:50.144 --> 22:52.278
that you're not paying attention to?

22:52.565 --> 22:54.461
Answer that,

22:54.486 --> 22:57.156
and you might find yourself
on a very different path...

22:58.166 --> 23:01.867
one that leads to Eloise Gardener.

23:08.129 --> 23:11.330
[MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ON STEREO]

23:12.968 --> 23:15.601
Oh, I didn't expect to see you so soon.

23:16.093 --> 23:17.313
That for me?

23:17.338 --> 23:19.238
It is.

23:20.125 --> 23:21.307
Right.

23:21.409 --> 23:25.678
So, uh, where's your
new pint-sized partner?

23:25.780 --> 23:27.980
[CHUCKLES] Lucy?

23:28.082 --> 23:29.648
She's home.

23:29.717 --> 23:32.388
So, turns out, there
was a Regina Mills...

23:32.794 --> 23:35.220
Adopted a baby boy in Boston.

23:35.468 --> 23:37.481
What? That's impossible.

23:39.018 --> 23:41.026
If you didn't think this was gonna work,

23:41.095 --> 23:43.128
why did you ask for help?

23:43.338 --> 23:48.475
Weaver, I asked for a
favor, not an interrogation.

23:49.588 --> 23:51.521
Here.

23:51.739 --> 23:52.971
Thank you.

23:52.996 --> 23:54.807
Yeah, what are old friends for?

23:54.909 --> 23:56.608
Favors.

23:59.036 --> 24:02.972
Favors that will one day be returned.

24:05.019 --> 24:06.652
You owe me one.

24:12.216 --> 24:14.827
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

24:14.852 --> 24:17.686
All those years...

24:17.711 --> 24:19.291
a blink of an eye for us,

24:19.351 --> 24:22.252
and you, you lived a
lifetime with Belle.

24:23.033 --> 24:25.604
[SIGHS] It's difficult to comprehend.

24:25.706 --> 24:27.580
You know, we had a good life.

24:29.143 --> 24:32.444
And it made me a new man.

24:32.469 --> 24:35.337
That's why I'm here in this realm.

24:35.394 --> 24:38.804
Finally ready to pass on
the power of the Dark One

24:39.306 --> 24:40.705
the right way.

24:40.825 --> 24:45.461
Well, it seems you <i> did</i> change.

24:45.486 --> 24:47.653
Well, change is inevitable.

24:47.678 --> 24:49.978
Slow and painful at
times, but inevitable.

24:50.003 --> 24:52.231
[SIGHS] Tell me about it.

24:52.333 --> 24:54.950
My son no longer needs me.

24:56.411 --> 24:58.170
But do you think this girl might.

24:59.840 --> 25:04.443
Oh, well, Drizella
has so much raw talent.

25:04.512 --> 25:05.811
She just needs a strong guide,

25:05.880 --> 25:07.346
someone to put her on the right path

25:07.371 --> 25:10.638
and teach her how to
stand up to her mother.

25:10.751 --> 25:13.427
I've heard dark tales
about this Lady Tremaine.

25:13.452 --> 25:15.107
She has no idea Drizella's here.

25:15.132 --> 25:16.060
Come on, Regina.

25:16.085 --> 25:18.682
You lived with a mother just like her.

25:18.979 --> 25:20.779
Do you really think you
would have gotten away

25:20.861 --> 25:22.795
with all of this without Cora knowing?

25:22.897 --> 25:25.497
Well... [SCOFFS]

25:28.466 --> 25:29.532
No.

25:29.557 --> 25:30.723
No.

25:31.441 --> 25:33.281
Take a piece of advice
from your former teacher

25:33.374 --> 25:35.207
and ask yourself this...

25:35.232 --> 25:39.201
Why would Tremaine want
her daughter to learn magic?

25:45.453 --> 25:48.954
That's my sister. Anastasia.

25:49.023 --> 25:50.856
Mother's favorite.

25:57.097 --> 25:58.397
[ <i> FLESH SQUISHES</i> ]

25:58.499 --> 26:00.432
What is she doing to her?

26:00.534 --> 26:02.634
[ <i> GRUNTS</i> ]

26:05.806 --> 26:07.005
Practicing.

26:07.107 --> 26:09.332
[ <i> FLESH SQUISHES</i> ]

26:09.357 --> 26:11.057
For what?

26:12.215 --> 26:15.013
For waking her up.

26:15.441 --> 26:20.052
She almost had my son's
heart ripped out before

26:20.120 --> 26:23.255
because the only way to wake Anastasia

26:23.324 --> 26:25.958
is by taking her heart

26:26.026 --> 26:30.095
and replacing it with one full of...

26:30.164 --> 26:31.497
Belief.

26:32.033 --> 26:33.866
My heart.

26:36.270 --> 26:37.446
I'm so sorry.

26:37.471 --> 26:39.057
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

26:39.283 --> 26:41.673
I always knew that she loved her more.

26:41.775 --> 26:45.310
[VOICE BREAKING] I guess
I just didn't realize

26:45.335 --> 26:48.403
how much until now.

26:53.254 --> 26:55.346
[INHALES SHARPLY] Oh, God.

26:56.891 --> 27:00.025
I'll never get away from her, will I?

27:00.094 --> 27:02.072
No matter what I do, she
always finds a way to hurt me.

27:02.096 --> 27:03.529
Oh, God! I'll never be free!

27:03.597 --> 27:05.731
Hey, hey. I can help.

27:05.756 --> 27:10.656
I promise I-I can protect your heart.

27:11.163 --> 27:13.505
There's only one way to protect me.

27:13.530 --> 27:16.865
Please, please...

27:16.890 --> 27:18.589
help me kill her.

27:21.282 --> 27:23.084
Drizella, no.

27:23.677 --> 27:27.719
I cannot let you go down that dark path.

27:27.788 --> 27:29.443
I thought you cared about me.

27:29.468 --> 27:32.057
That's why I'm saying no.

27:32.159 --> 27:33.761
[SCOFFS]

27:34.316 --> 27:35.448
You know what?

27:35.473 --> 27:37.540
That's exactly what my
mother used to tell me.

27:37.731 --> 27:39.331
And if you're not going to help me,

27:39.400 --> 27:42.234
I know a prince who will.

27:49.843 --> 27:53.045
What pieces do I already have?

28:14.535 --> 28:16.731
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

28:44.956 --> 28:48.299
_

29:30.852 --> 29:32.652
It's like a painting.

29:32.720 --> 29:36.389
A mother mourns the loss
of her only loved child.

29:36.916 --> 29:38.530
What are you doing here, Drizella?

29:38.555 --> 29:41.423
I told Prince Gregor everything,

29:41.576 --> 29:44.577
like how you want to rip my heart out.

29:44.602 --> 29:47.303
I won't let you harm my bride.

29:49.370 --> 29:50.670
REGINA: That's enough.

29:54.508 --> 29:56.275
You don't want to do this, Drizella.

29:56.377 --> 29:58.553
No, <i>you</i> don't want to do this.

29:58.578 --> 30:01.920
You refuse to understand that
we have a different story.

30:02.241 --> 30:04.975
The pain like mine can't be washed away.

30:06.788 --> 30:10.636
You know, I've been trying my
whole life to win your approval.

30:10.661 --> 30:14.293
But now I realize I'm
never going to get it

30:14.362 --> 30:15.832
because I'm not her.

30:15.942 --> 30:18.376
You're most certainly not.

30:19.051 --> 30:21.121
Drizella, come with me.

30:23.655 --> 30:26.423
If you kill your
mother, you'll regret it.

30:27.134 --> 30:28.925
You know what?

30:29.027 --> 30:30.501
You're right.

30:31.563 --> 30:35.832
But I didn't bring Gregor
here to kill my mother.

30:35.901 --> 30:38.601
I brought him here to
kill something else.

30:39.608 --> 30:41.204
What are you talking about?

30:41.343 --> 30:43.743
I can't let my mother
have what she wants.

30:56.012 --> 30:57.511
Drizella.

31:05.864 --> 31:07.564
What have you done?

31:07.938 --> 31:10.577
What both of you were most afraid of...

31:12.070 --> 31:14.021
I turned my heart black.

31:15.540 --> 31:19.309
And now it's of no use to you, Mother.

31:19.378 --> 31:20.610
You failed.

31:20.635 --> 31:23.446
What do you want from
me? Congratulations?

31:23.548 --> 31:25.081
No.

31:25.370 --> 31:27.103
I want you to suffer.

31:28.076 --> 31:30.487
Regina taught me things you never would,

31:30.555 --> 31:34.053
and I don't just mean magic tricks.

31:34.078 --> 31:36.326
She taught me how to seek revenge.

31:36.428 --> 31:39.629
A little thing called the Dark Curse.

31:40.100 --> 31:43.400
Drizella, that was a warning.

31:43.468 --> 31:45.802
A curse is never worth the cost.

31:45.904 --> 31:47.771
It is to me.

31:53.512 --> 31:55.812
Death is too merciful for you, Mother.

31:57.382 --> 32:00.183
I'm going to take you to another realm

32:00.252 --> 32:04.054
where I can plant a seed
of pain in your life.

32:04.122 --> 32:08.224
It'll start small, and it will grow

32:08.326 --> 32:15.532
until everything you see,
you breathe, you feel is pain.

32:16.711 --> 32:18.256
REGINA: No.

32:18.788 --> 32:20.778
Listen to me.

32:21.473 --> 32:23.825
I wanted to help you.

32:24.209 --> 32:25.508
But if you go through with this,

32:25.610 --> 32:29.245
I will do whatever it takes to stop you.

32:29.314 --> 32:32.082
Heroes can always break curses.

32:34.119 --> 32:36.853
Well, then, I guess I'd better find

32:36.922 --> 32:39.489
a way to make mine unbreakable.

32:39.558 --> 32:43.293
Thank you for your final lesson.

32:47.737 --> 32:49.099
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

32:49.201 --> 32:51.067
[CELLPHONE THUDS]

32:51.169 --> 32:53.002
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYS ON STEREO]

32:53.105 --> 32:54.504
Oh, my!

32:54.606 --> 32:56.086
- There's no one here.
- [DOOR CLOSES]

32:56.174 --> 33:00.210
Guess I must have missed
your little Avengers assembly.

33:00.278 --> 33:03.780
Shame, since I may have found more dirt.

33:04.711 --> 33:08.384
I'm gonna pour us something
from the top shelf...

33:08.487 --> 33:09.586
and then I'll talk.

33:09.654 --> 33:12.422
[CHUCKLES DRYLY] This better be good.

33:14.459 --> 33:16.860
[LIQUID POURS]

33:22.132 --> 33:27.502
So... what did you find?

33:29.174 --> 33:31.774
Actually, this is all
about what you found.

33:33.455 --> 33:35.254
What are you talking about?

33:36.448 --> 33:38.982
See, I needed you to go on
your little adventure today

33:39.315 --> 33:40.794
with Lucy.

33:40.819 --> 33:42.919
I needed you to start asking yourself,

33:42.988 --> 33:45.588
"What if the photo is real?

33:45.657 --> 33:49.792
What if all of Henry's
fairy tales were true?"

33:49.861 --> 33:52.662
Because once you start asking
yourself those questions

33:52.697 --> 33:55.165
[DISTORTED VOICE] your
little brain is all warmed up,

33:55.267 --> 33:59.269
and I can push it right over the edge.

34:02.207 --> 34:05.575
Did you put something in my drink?

34:21.143 --> 34:22.609
I love you, too.

34:25.063 --> 34:27.263
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

34:29.734 --> 34:31.900
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

34:32.003 --> 34:35.170
Welcome back... Regina.

34:37.775 --> 34:39.509
Drizella.

34:39.897 --> 34:41.530
Oh, did you miss me?

34:41.554 --> 34:42.911
[GRUNTS]

34:43.014 --> 34:45.215
Oh, sorry!

34:45.739 --> 34:47.449
Land Without Magic.

34:47.629 --> 34:51.531
Well, just enough to wake you up.

34:51.556 --> 34:54.657
[CELLPHONE RINGING, BUZZING]

34:56.061 --> 34:59.329
[EXHALES SHARPLY] Henry.

34:59.431 --> 35:02.932
I... wouldn't answer that if I were you.

35:03.034 --> 35:04.267
Henry can't know about this.

35:04.336 --> 35:06.102
Then why the hell did you wake me up?

35:06.171 --> 35:07.270
Mm.

35:07.372 --> 35:11.040
Your mind might be a
little foggy from your nap.

35:11.109 --> 35:12.442
Just give it a minute.

35:12.958 --> 35:14.824
[RINGING, BUZZING CONTINUE]

35:18.483 --> 35:20.016
There it is.

35:20.041 --> 35:21.607
It's all coming back.

35:25.397 --> 35:27.901
Now, you told me

35:27.926 --> 35:30.827
that a hero always breaks the curse,

35:30.895 --> 35:33.263
so I made mine hero-proof.

35:33.298 --> 35:37.200
Do you remember what I did
right before the curse was cast

35:37.269 --> 35:41.304
and why you can't ever
allow it to be broken?

35:47.967 --> 35:49.879
You do remember.

35:50.230 --> 35:51.881
If the curse is broken,

35:51.983 --> 35:57.253
something very bad happens
to the people you love.

35:57.278 --> 35:59.555
You should be proud.

35:59.702 --> 36:01.668
You know you're a great teacher

36:01.693 --> 36:05.528
when the student surpasses the master.

36:08.833 --> 36:10.900
And what do you want, huh?

36:11.002 --> 36:13.736
You want a gold star?

36:13.805 --> 36:15.838
Or did you just wake me to gloat?

36:15.940 --> 36:18.308
As much fun as that is, no.

36:18.376 --> 36:19.409
[GLASS THUDS]

36:19.434 --> 36:22.111
I woke you up because I need your help.

36:22.180 --> 36:24.781
I am on the verge of showing my mother

36:24.883 --> 36:27.615
what true suffering is.

36:27.751 --> 36:30.987
I can't have anyone
breaking the curse now.

36:31.089 --> 36:32.555
You mean...

36:34.926 --> 36:39.996
Henry and Jaci... Cinderella.

36:40.098 --> 36:43.399
We both know you will
do whatever it takes

36:43.501 --> 36:46.608
to stop True Love's Kiss from happening.

36:48.606 --> 36:52.508
That shouldn't be too hard
for the Evil Queen, right?

36:52.610 --> 36:54.544
After all,

36:54.646 --> 36:57.613
breaking hearts is kind
of what you're best at.

37:05.924 --> 37:09.759
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

37:14.399 --> 37:17.210
REGINA: After everything
I've been through,

37:17.235 --> 37:19.635
I still haven't learned my lesson.

37:19.704 --> 37:24.740
How could I let a girl with that
much pain anywhere near magic?

37:24.809 --> 37:27.543
How could I be so stupid?

37:27.612 --> 37:29.123
You were just trying to
see the best in someone.

37:29.147 --> 37:30.446
That's never stupid.

37:30.471 --> 37:33.826
It's a nice sentiment,
but this wasn't about her.

37:33.851 --> 37:35.618
It's about me.

37:36.608 --> 37:38.354
And you, actually.

37:38.655 --> 37:40.056
Me?

37:40.259 --> 37:43.661
I came to this land to help you,

37:43.686 --> 37:46.162
because I thought you needed it.

37:48.266 --> 37:51.634
But you're not the kid who
left Storybrooke anymore.

37:53.118 --> 37:54.603
You can fight your own battles now.

37:54.672 --> 37:56.439
And when you can't, you have Ella.

37:56.618 --> 37:58.785
You are so wrong.

37:59.263 --> 38:01.010
I do need you.

38:01.252 --> 38:03.519
You're the first person who loved me,

38:04.028 --> 38:08.474
the <i> only</i> person
for many, many years.

38:11.703 --> 38:12.789
So, yeah, yeah.

38:12.814 --> 38:16.488
I can take care of bullies
or brigands or whatever.

38:18.696 --> 38:21.397
But I will always need you.

38:21.774 --> 38:26.068
And I... I need you.

38:27.805 --> 38:31.373
Living in Storybrooke without you is...

38:31.476 --> 38:33.876
I couldn't stand it.

38:39.250 --> 38:43.539
Whatever else I'm supposed
to do with my life...

38:46.057 --> 38:48.657
I'm your mother first.

38:50.328 --> 38:56.067
'Cause without that, I
just don't know how to be.

39:00.404 --> 39:02.605
[SIGHS]

39:04.976 --> 39:06.842
[VEHICLE APPROACHES]

39:17.822 --> 39:19.378
HENRY: Hey.

39:19.403 --> 39:22.158
Well, you will be happy to know

39:22.260 --> 39:25.094
that things with Jacinda...

39:25.119 --> 39:26.785
went pretty well.

39:29.534 --> 39:32.067
Guess we'll just have to see
where that goes, won't we?

39:33.037 --> 39:36.338
Keep me in the loop. I'm
pretty good with advice.

39:37.975 --> 39:41.043
And how are you with
precocious little girls?

39:41.112 --> 39:44.046
Is Lucy... off this fantasy of hers yet?

39:44.966 --> 39:47.622
You know, uh, I was thinking.

39:49.735 --> 39:53.794
Maybe it would help if she
knew a little more about you.

39:55.259 --> 40:00.429
You know, like, who your mother is.

40:00.608 --> 40:03.442
I haven't told her this

40:03.467 --> 40:05.245
because I didn't want
to add fuel to the fire,

40:05.269 --> 40:10.773
but I was...

40:10.842 --> 40:14.808
I was born in prison
just like my character.

40:16.647 --> 40:19.615
Except I was never adopted.
I grew up in the system.

40:21.485 --> 40:23.385
Like Emma did.

40:26.390 --> 40:27.649
In your book.

40:28.659 --> 40:29.659
You read my book?

40:29.760 --> 40:31.493
I picked up a copy.

40:31.930 --> 40:33.239
It was really good.

40:33.264 --> 40:35.831
Nah. It's... it's okay.

40:35.900 --> 40:38.801
I mean, you don't have to say that.

40:40.538 --> 40:42.149
It used to bother me
that no one liked it,

40:42.173 --> 40:46.242
but I started to realize
it doesn't matter.

40:46.646 --> 40:49.111
I think I wrote it just for myself.

40:52.704 --> 40:54.360
Growing up an orphan,
all I ever dreamt of

40:54.385 --> 40:56.385
was having a mom.

40:58.189 --> 40:59.265
And I wanted it so badly

40:59.290 --> 41:02.358
that I found a way to give myself two.

41:05.865 --> 41:07.544
Henry, I...

41:07.583 --> 41:09.182
What? What?

41:16.107 --> 41:19.775
I'm just so glad

41:19.877 --> 41:21.644
we're getting to know each other.

41:23.281 --> 41:24.880
Me, too.

